cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with saliency maps, which are commonly used in computer vision to interpret model predictions. The use of Bayesian optimisation also suggests a machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes an approach for generating saliency maps for black-box models, which could fall under the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The use of natural language processing techniques to generate saliency maps could also place this paper in the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category. Finally, the sampling-based approach used in the paper could suggest a Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
